1. Discard unstaged local changes:
git restore <file>

2. Remove from staging without losing changes:
git restore --staged <file>

3. Fix wrong commit message (not pushed):
git commit --amend -m "Correct commit message"

4. View commit history (readable):
git log --oneline --graph --decorate

5. Set global name & email:
git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "you@example.com"

6. View unstaged edits:
git diff

7. Switch to branch:
git switch feature/login

8. Restore deleted branch (not pushed delete):
git reflog
git branch feature-ui <commit_hash>

9. Upload local commits:
git push

10. Fetch without merge:
git fetch

11. Create & switch new branch:
git switch -c search-filter

12. Remove committed API-key file from history:
git filter-branch --force --index-filter "git rm --cached --ignore-unmatch <file>" --prune-empty --tag-name-filter cat -- --all

13. List local + remote branches:
git branch -a

14. Merge feature/signup into main:
git switch main
git merge feature/signup

15. Resolve merge conflict:
git add app.js
git commit

16. Ignore .log / node_modules:
(Add them to .gitignore file manually)

17. Who last changed line 25:
git blame -L 25,25 script.py

18. Save work before switching:
git stash

19. Restore stash:
git stash pop

20. Delete branch locally:
git branch -d feature/test

21. Delete merged branch safely:
git switch main
git branch -d feature-ui

22. Force delete unmerged branch:
git branch -D feature-experiment

23. Delete feature-ui while on feature-login (ensure you're not on that branch):
git switch feature-login
git branch -d feature-ui

24. Check if branch is merged before deletions:
git branch --merged | grep bugfix-footer

25. Delete multiple merged branches in one command:
git branch -d feature-a feature-b feature-c

26. Clone a remote repo:
git clone <repository_url>

27. See connected remotes:
git remote -v

28. Add new remote:
git remote add <remote_name> <repository_url>

29. Remove remote:
git remote remove <remote_name>

30. Rename a remote:
git remote rename <old_name> <new_name>

31. Fetch updates from remote only:
git fetch <remote_name>

32. Pull and merge latest changes:
git pull <remote_name> <branch_name>

33. Push local commits:
git push <remote_name> <branch_name>

34. Push first time and set upstream:
git push -u <remote_name> <branch_name>

35. Change remote URL:
git remote set-url <remote_name> <new_repository_url>

36. List all remote branches:
git ls-remote --heads <remote_name>

37. Remove deleted remote branches from local view:
git fetch --prune

38. Fetch specific branch from remote:
git fetch <remote_name> <branch_name>

39. Fetch specific branch and store as local branch:
git fetch <remote_name> <branch_name>:<local_branch_name>

40. Show detailed remote info:
git remote show <remote_name>

41. Rebase local branch onto remote branch:
git rebase <remote_name>/<branch_name>
 
